			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-6bc0c69d-538f-452b-b5a2-a6e27f5c14d8">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#6bc0c69d-538f-452b-b5a2-a6e27f5c14d8" aria-controls="6bc0c69d-538f-452b-b5a2-a6e27f5c14d8" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="395ae3c0-4825-4976-bb71-72c179ce93f6">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">[orcpplink]Annual survey run #2 vending, coffee carts and food concessions Commission for the Blind 01/08/2026</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="6bc0c69d-538f-452b-b5a2-a6e27f5c14d8" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClass099E4D7A53004C50A349137236123135"><p style="margin&#58;0in;"><span style="font-family&#58;roboto;font-size&#58;12pt;">H</span><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">ello OrCPP Members,</span></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Did you know the
Commission for the Blind has a program designed to help Oregonians who are
legally blind start food concession businesses? It’s called the Business
Enterprise Program (BEP) and their mission is to provide food service and
vending opportunities in government buildings across the State to Oregonians
who are blind. <br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Have you or your
coworkers been asking for vending machines, a coffee cart, or some other type
of food concession in your workplace? <br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">If the answer is
‘yes’, please complete the 2025 survey (<a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//www.surveymonkey.com/r/5JBMTPZ&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cac344122e73f44beafcb08de4ecdd32d%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c639034843084683001%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=AVwP1PZihXV/7iLJ0Flss0R2gqUIIVqZzrRYcWhWrx4%3D&amp;reserved=0">https&#58;//www.surveymonkey.com/r/5JBMTPZ</a>)
and reach out to the BEP Business Development Specialist Ryan McBee at <a href="mailto&#58;ryan.mcbee@ocb.oregon.gov">ryan.mcbee@ocb.oregon.gov</a> to start
the conversation.</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Why do I need to
complete the survey?<br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">You’ll not only help
us establish more business opportunities for Oregonians who are blind, but the
survey provides you with an easy mechanism to fulfill legislatively required
annual reporting&#58; <br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;"><a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//oregon.public.law/statutes/ors_346.530&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cac344122e73f44beafcb08de4ecdd32d%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c639034843084713175%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=Hk95KAtsGBnT4HIRsJpuU1LDAc9Z13evtNAAiSewEoI%3D&amp;reserved=0">ORS
346.530 </a>&#160;now requires that agencies and political subdivisions
according to &#160;<a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//oregon.public.law/statutes/ors_346.510&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cac344122e73f44beafcb08de4ecdd32d%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c639034843084732274%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=UT8xzd7vqP7VlsKXUHHnClGur/ZvciFEN6VfJaxhalY%3D&amp;reserved=0">ORS
346.510 </a>&#160;“annually notify the Commission for the Blind in writing of
any and all existing locations where vending facilities are in operation or
where vending facilities might properly and satisfactorily be operated”.&#160; </p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Thank you for
helping create business opportunities for Oregonians who are blind. If you have
any questions regarding the survey, please reach out&#58; <br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">​Ron Stewart,
Business Enterprise Program Director<br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Oregon Commission
for the Blind</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;"><a href="mailto&#58;ron.w.stewart@ocb.oregon.gov">ron.w.stewart@ocb.oregon.gov</a></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">971-673-1588<br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-b5f0a5fb-bd7a-48c9-ba2b-ffc1ff3e4b00">
				<h4>
