				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="724c73a1-d8fd-4a5b-8085-985ebdedcef5" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClass42B216ECFFEC46A1BA73697669AC07E7"><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;roboto;font-size&#58;12pt;"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;14.6667px;">​The Oregon Forward
Program is sending this notification as a courtesy to all Authorized
Purchasers. Price Agreement 8274 for Flagger Services has been amended.<br></span></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;14.6667px;">Price Agreement 8274
has been amended to revise Attachment A Specifications and Position
Descriptions, Attachment B Schedule of Services, Attachment D-1 DAS Approved
Ordering Instrument State Agencies, Attachment D-2 DAS Approved Ordering
Instrument Public Body, &#160;and Attachment F Contact Information for the
Parties.</span></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;14.6667px;">The Price Agreement
amendment 6 and any documents related to the Price Agreement is now available
on OregonBuys (</span><a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//oregonbuys.gov/bso/external/purchaseorder/poSummary.sdo?docId%3D8274%26releaseNbr%3D0%26external%3Dtrue%26parentUrl%3Dclose&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cb385ce21991c4cc97b2308de39cead3c%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c639011756989756046%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=9nDe5PuX6Svv0BlxuFU3Gatq1CQJXLoHY5ejBmPniSQ%3D&amp;reserved=0"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;14.6667px;">8274</span></a><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;14.6667px;">).
In OregonBuys refer to “Attachments” tab for the current Attachments.</span></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;14.6667px;">For more information
regarding this message, contact Rena Montes, Oregon Forward Program Contracts
Manager, at 503-507-1246 or via email </span><a href="mailto&#58;info.ofp@das.oregon.gov"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;14.6667px;">info.ofp@das.oregon.gov</span></a><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;14.6667px;">
.</span></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-73851837-1a82-434c-9230-f7c72b260ed8">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#73851837-1a82-434c-9230-f7c72b260ed8" aria-controls="73851837-1a82-434c-9230-f7c72b260ed8" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="c1ffad51-664d-4a55-b5ca-de5df02e15ed">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">[orcpplink]Vending, coffee carts and food concessions, Commission for the Blind annual survey 12/08/2025</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="73851837-1a82-434c-9230-f7c72b260ed8" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClass08AEA05620224537B054AD3EC8E6B5D0"><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">​Hello OrCPP Members,<br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Did you know the
Commission for the Blind has a program designed to help Oregonians who are
legally blind start food concession businesses? It’s called the Business
Enterprise Program (BEP) and their mission is to provide food service and
vending opportunities in government buildings across the State to Oregonians
who are blind. </p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Have you or your
coworkers been asking for vending machines, a coffee cart, or some other type
of food concession in your workplace? </p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">If the answer is
‘yes’, please complete the 2025 survey (<a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//www.surveymonkey.com/r/5JBMTPZ&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cb10db6b783484eabe80c08de369adf98%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c639008235973678225%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=HntCcoccY7LMvC7Yc7zAYkYhUS%2BsDw%2BUFrRcwYnp%2BNU%3D&amp;reserved=0">https&#58;//www.surveymonkey.com/r/5JBMTPZ</a>)
and reach out to the BEP Business Development Specialist Ryan McBee at <a href="mailto&#58;ryan.mcbee@ocb.oregon.gov">ryan.mcbee@ocb.oregon.gov</a> to start
the conversation.</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Why do I need to
complete a survey?</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">You’ll not only help
us establish more business opportunities for Oregonians who are blind, but the
survey provides you with an easy mechanism to fulfill legislatively required
annual reporting&#58; </p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;"><a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//oregon.public.law/statutes/ors_346.530&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cb10db6b783484eabe80c08de369adf98%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c639008235973701607%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=fWkHpWpIjEqNcs63px2YYqfevfwScyB7gkyqQ/9ThDs%3D&amp;reserved=0">ORS
346.530 </a>&#160;now requires that agencies and political subdivisions
according to &#160;<a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//oregon.public.law/statutes/ors_346.510&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cb10db6b783484eabe80c08de369adf98%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c639008235973718336%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=C0hAqCroIp3KnyFsjFESv4GJOu2NDFgh5%2Bb4HndGAKE%3D&amp;reserved=0">ORS
346.510 </a>&#160;“annually notify the Commission for the Blind in writing of
any and all existing locations where vending facilities are in operation or
where vending facilities might properly and satisfactorily be operated”.&#160; </p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Thank you for
helping create business opportunities for Oregonians who are blind. If you have
any questions regarding the survey, please reach out&#58; </p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Ron Stewart,
Business Enterprise Program Director</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Oregon Commission
for the Blind</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;"><a href="mailto&#58;ron.w.stewart@ocb.oregon.gov">ron.w.stewart@ocb.oregon.gov</a></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">971-673-1588<br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-a6d22970-6f1f-468d-8ec5-cbc8103abe99">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#a6d22970-6f1f-468d-8ec5-cbc8103abe99" aria-controls="a6d22970-6f1f-468d-8ec5-cbc8103abe99" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="51ab3788-d2b1-47e3-a73b-3e5fd90ecf06">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">[orcpplink]Custom laser engraving for the holidays from Oregon Corrections Enterprises 12/01/2025</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="a6d22970-6f1f-468d-8ec5-cbc8103abe99" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClassE38C21EE8AD84EAB8699751D345ABCFD"><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">​As the
holiday season approaches, it’s the perfect time to start planning unique and
thoughtful gifts for your teams and partners. At OCE Sign Shop, we’re proud to
offer high-quality laser engraving services on a variety of metal items, from
water bottles and hydro flasks to coffee cups and travel mugs. <br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Our
recent work includes custom engravings for top organizations like the Oregon
Department of Forestry, Oregon State Police, Oregon Parks and Recreation
Department, and many more. Whether you're looking to add your logo or a special
message, we’ve got you covered!</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Why
choose OCE Sign Shop?</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Custom,
professional engraving on durable metal surfaces</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Versatility&#58;
Perfect for water bottles, mugs, and travel cups</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Personalized
designs for employee gifts, giveaways, or holiday tokens</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Support
for local businesses and state organizations</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Our
featured items &amp; pricing&#58;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;"><span style="font-weight&#58;bold;">﻿</span></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">&#160;16oz coffee mug - $25</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">32oz
hydro flask</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">(Straw
Top) - $30</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">40oz
hydro flask</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">(single
top) - $35</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Get
ahead of the holiday rush.</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">Make
this year’s gifting special by ordering custom-engraved items now. Let us help
you create memorable gifts that reflect your brand and appreciation.</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;"><span style="color&#58;#403f42;">Contact </span><a href="mailto&#58;ocesignshop@oce.oregon.gov"><span style="font-weight&#58;bold;">ocesignshop@oce.oregon.gov</span></a><span style="color&#58;#403f42;"> today to discuss your holiday orders and secure your
spot before our schedule</span></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;color&#58;#403f42;">fills
up!<br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-b7eda16f-ac32-41ba-b734-9366ec02d82a">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#b7eda16f-ac32-41ba-b734-9366ec02d82a" aria-controls="b7eda16f-ac32-41ba-b734-9366ec02d82a" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="3f94fb78-ba6e-4c0a-ba38-86a4f0b1a7bf">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">[orcpplink]GovRAMP Phase 1: Accept program playbook 11/20/2025</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="b7eda16f-ac32-41ba-b734-9366ec02d82a" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClassF59921764C864E93AFF7EF052711FEDD"><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">​DAS State
Procurement Services (SPS) and Enterprise Information (EIS) Services Cyber
Security Services (CSS) are announcing that, effective immediately, Oregon is
participating in the GovRAMP Phase 1&#58; Accept Program initiative. <br></p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">GovRAMP, formerly
known as StateRAMP, is a national initiative to manage vendor compliance with
cybersecurity standards and requirements.</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">What Does This Mean
for State Buyers? </p><ul style="direction&#58;ltr;unicode-bidi&#58;embed;margin-top&#58;0in;margin-bottom&#58;0in;"><li style="margin-top&#58;0px;margin-bottom&#58;0px;vertical-align&#58;middle;"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">The GovRAMP Phase 1&#58; Accept
     Program applies to all agencies subject to EIS authority for information
     security under </span><a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//www.oregonlegislature.gov/bills_laws/ors/ors276A.html&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cd32d533ca927485689f708de285d4ae2%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c638992578364495416%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=qLvQMUURQrEnyq1TgSlPx5w9Ze8rUZ4aCKfPQBQuSKE%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">ORS 276A.300</span></a><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">.</span></li><li style="margin-top&#58;0px;margin-bottom&#58;0px;vertical-align&#58;middle;"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">All new solicitation and
     contract documents for cloud-based products or hosted services must now
     include new provisions. </span></li><li style="margin-top&#58;0px;margin-bottom&#58;0px;vertical-align&#58;middle;"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">While we work to update
     statewide templates, use the attached GovRAMP Phase 1&#58; Accept Program
     Playbook for the new provisions and instructions. If you have an </span><a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//oregonbuys.gov/bso/&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cd32d533ca927485689f708de285d4ae2%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c638992578364516387%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=5AbkZKcKw8mhSmIt58LKYdMtl5K7m0xh1yxPriMymHg%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">OregonBuys®</span></a><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;"> account, you can also access
     it by logging in&#160;and clicking “GovRAMP Playbook for State
     Agencies”&#160;under the “News” section on the home screen. </span></li><li style="margin-top&#58;0px;margin-bottom&#58;0px;vertical-align&#58;middle;"><span style="font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">Existing contracts and
     solicitations do not need to be amended with the new provisions at this
     time. </span></li></ul><p style="margin&#58;0in 0in 0in 0.375in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">In the next few
days, we will also notify vendors about these new provisions and inform them of
the optional third-party verifications and certifications offered by
GovRAMP.&#160; </p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">&#160;</p><p style="margin&#58;0in;font-family&#58;calibri;font-size&#58;11pt;">For more information
about GovRAMP, visit the <a href="https&#58;//gcc02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https&#58;//programs.stateramp.org/oregon-and-stateramp/&amp;data=05%7c02%7cKimberley.wisdom%40oregon.gov%7cd32d533ca927485689f708de285d4ae2%7caa3f6932fa7c47b4a0cea598cad161cf%7c0%7c0%7c638992578364531448%7cUnknown%7cTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7c0%7c%7c%7c&amp;sdata=%2BTRAA1vucZDz%2BQeAjprcUAi1NyJoB2z%2B3qrniwmNQyA%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank">Oregon
GovRAMP website</a>. If you have questions about Oregon’s participation in the
initiative, visit the <a href="/eis/cyber-security-services/Pages/default.aspx" target="_blank">CSS
website</a> or contact ORCPP at <a href="mailto&#58;Info.ORCPP@das.oregon.gov" target="_blank">Info.ORCPP@das.oregon.gov</a><br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-3db54217-0154-4c1f-917e-520cd31e34d0">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#3db54217-0154-4c1f-917e-520cd31e34d0" aria-controls="3db54217-0154-4c1f-917e-520cd31e34d0" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="3b08946f-a648-4e05-b3db-386b5289640a">
